{
  "uuid": "be6d0acd447826a37b80c2dd0b2df848",
  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Technical Project Manager",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Onsite Project Manager to work directly with customer mainly in Singapore, and remote/offshore development teams.</li><li>Lead multiple teams to deliver projects on time, on budget, in scope and delight the customers</li><li>Analyze clients requirements and work out strategic planning, Develop program strategies and goals which match with the strategic and product roadmap of customer.</li><li>Coordinate and organize project activities to deliver working software to production, aligning with the product roadmap.</li><li>Main coordination and escalation point for the team</li><li>Manage project development and implementation. Manage the project schedule and track activities to successful delivery.</li><li>Manage the delivery process and ensure all project documentations are filed and kept.</li><li>Manage project risks and dependencies, recommending workaround solutions to customers to meet delivery timelines.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>Bachelors degree in Computer Science, Computer Engineering, or a related field.</li><li>Valid PMP certification with at least 7 years of experience in a Project Manager role, including a minimum of 3 years in Digital Transformation projects/programs.</li><li>Proficient in Agile software development methodologies (Scrum, Kanban, Lean, XP).</li><li>Experienced in process change and adoption across technical delivery teams.</li><li>Familiar with Enterprise Integration and Application Design patterns.</li><li>Skilled in scheduling and tracking using open-source tools (e.g., JIRA and Confluence).</li><li>Ability to work effectively in a team environment, including onsite/offshore communication.</li><li>Excellent communication skills.</li><li>Customer-facing experience is a must.</li><li>Experience in Healthcare or AI/AR projects/programs in healthcare is a plus.</li></ul>",
